iles as he rdaughter comes to her. She wraps her arms around her in a light embrace.*** Its good to see you my dear as well.<br>
***She looks to her with unblinking eyes*** Why are we focusing on Eris? Well, lets see, where she goes, trouble follows...always. She isnt here my dear to spoil the party...but to start some major damage here upon the Olympians. Hades hath no fury like Eris pissed. Her temper surpases anyone of the Olympians, including Zeus's and Ares's. My child, have you not been informed...she is the worst, and her little games arent little.<br>
No game that she has started ever ended with a small kaboom, more like a giant bang. <br>
Shes not here to merely throw around insults and ego trips. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/upersephoneqofu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>PersephoneQofU</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 93<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(10/24/01 10:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=52>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/mirellasb/mags/susanpress047.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> not to be afraid</span><hr size=1> ::looks at Eris up and down and back at her mother:: <br>
<br>
I know what she's done mother, am I supposed to be scared? ::laughs confidently:: I've seen her damage mother, and I'm not afraid of her &quot;tactics&quot; ::makes the quotation makrs with her fingers::<br>
<br>
I live in the Underworld mother, I've seen MUCH worse stuff than the things Eris has done in the past. And besides, the only temper I get worried by is Zeus' and Hades, no one here had seen Hades at his worse like I have. I'm his wife. I should know :shudders at  the thought::<br>
<br>
Come mother, lets go say hello to the couple ::escorts her by her elbow over to the newlyweds:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uixlordhadesxi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IX Lord Hades XI</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 129<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(10/24/01 11:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=53>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> In Tartarus...</span><hr size=1> ::Hades was standing on the top terrace of his palace.  He felt someone returning to his realm, someone very powerful. After a few moments of scrying he realized it was Hecate.  He stepped off the terrace overlooking practically all of Tartarus and to walked the gates of his palace.  He walked for a little bit and decided to meet Hecate on her pathway in.  He stepped in front of the path of her dragons, with that infamous smirk on his face::<br>
<br>
&quot;You're back early?  All go well?&quot;  ::Asking as though he knew what went on.  He had an 'idea'.:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uxxdemeterxx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>xxDemeterxx</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(10/25/01 12:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=54>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Being pulled</span><hr size=1> ***She stopped as her daughter stopped her on the way to the newlyweds and headed back to her seat. The newlyweds would come to her as they should go to alll the Gods and Goddesses if they were respectable. She smiled and shook her head at the innocence of her daughter. Though in the underworld for half the year, it hasnt destroyed her, and for that, Demeter was happy. Though she didnt like the nieveity of her daughter on the part of Eris. Though not intimidating to look at, Eris did wallop quite a punch, she was the worse off all Olympians as far as anger was concerened. Far worse then Zeus and even her brother Hades. They were pussycats compared to her young neice. Perhaps it would be better for her daughter to be in the Underworld with Hades during this time, for Persephone is drastically underestimating the Goddess of Discord.*** <br>
 **She shrugged with a slight sigh, she was feeling rather old this day, but she couldnt leave, no tyet, not until she knew what that Eris was up to...** <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uvvvthegoddesshecatevvv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>VVV The Goddess Hecate VVV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 50<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(10/25/01 7:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=55>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Being pulled</span><hr size=1> spotting Hades in the way of her dragons she quickly pulls on the reins causeing them to come to a complete hault giving the little charriot a small jerk<br>
