<br>
She knew that everyone ignoring Eris would piss her off even more, then maybe she'd actually get to the point of all this.<br>
<br>
&quot;Why hello Dear Uncle.&quot; She gave a wavering smile to Poseidon. The war over Athens took place not so long ago, which meant that both of the Olympians were still a bit harsh in words towards one another, Athena tried her best to keep them simple.<br>
<br>
She then heard the comment about Hera not enjoying Zeus' company. She linked her arm with her Father's in a sense of reassurance to him that she would always be there. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uthegreatapollo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The Great Apollo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 102<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(10/25/01 2:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=58>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Something is a wry...</span><hr size=1> Apollo shook the hair from his head, and excused himself from a heated conversation in the middle of the room about the building tension between Greece and Troy. Spotting his dear sister and step-mother he waltzed his way over to them with a smile.<br>
<br>
He sipped his wine, looking over the goblet to meet the dark eyes of his silvery sister. Himself...he was glowing with his usual golden warmth. He said:<br>
<br>
&quot;Is it me, or is something just not right about this?...&quot; he turned his head and looked to his step, Eris. His face scrunched up, she was to much like Ares, and everyone knew how well the &quot;pacifist&quot; and the &quot;warlord&quot; got along. He looked back to his sister and mother, a look of slight disgust upon him. He stuck out his tounge and laughed, again sipping his wine.<br>
<br>
&quot;I hope she doesn't try anything...opprobrious... I mean, it is a wedding. But knowing Eris, she has something up her sleeve just waiting to spill out onto the floor.&quot;<br>
<br>
He looked at Artemis once more before taking her by the wrist and basically dragging her over to Athena.<br>
